summary: Like, the end moral of Game of Thrones is lionizing intimate partner violence. Tyrion murdered a sex worker for betraying him...
body:
Like, the end moral of Game of Thrones is lionizing intimate partner violence.

Tyrion murdered a sex worker for betraying him and sleeping with his father? That’s okay, it was justified and he felt kind of bad about it afterwards!

Sansa was physically abused by her first fiance, preyed on by her adult male protector as a child, and raped and tortured by her husband? That’s okay, because it made her stronger (and just as manipulative and selfish as them)!

Dany was physically and sexually abused by her brother, raped by her husband, threatened with rape by countless men, and murdered by the love of her life? That’s okay, because she was crazy in the end and needed to be put down for the good of the realm!

summary: I cannot beLIEVE there are actually people saying Sansa should’ve bent the knee because Bran would’ve been a Stark king. Or...
body:
I cannot beLIEVE there are actually people saying Sansa should’ve bent the knee because Bran would’ve been a Stark king. Or rather, I guess I can, but fuck y’all.

Sansa is the oldest living child of Ned Stark and has consistently shown herself capable of tactics and leading Winterfell. Expecting her to kneel to her little brother, who isn’t even really her little brother anymore, with the full knowledge that if and when his reign ends some other random person will take the throne, is absurd. If Jon had said, “no, the north must remain an independent kingdom” those same people would be cheering him on. It’s just so fucking transparent.

body:
This stupid post has been in my drafts for like three years. So what the hell.

My brother once wanted to play a drinking game. I told him we should watch Shrek and drink every time we were reminded of Sandor, Sansa and Arya.

He thought I was bananas but:

Beautiful red head locked up with a monster:

Day dreaming about

But the only one who made an effort was not some handsome knight. And it was so not a fairytale 

And though the guy was cranky, liked to drink, and was scary and could kick all kinds of ass

He was also pretty screwed over by life

And had sidekick but that he loved a lot and went on lots of trekking adventures with, even though they pissed each other off:

Also

And don’t forget creep with a goatee wanting to “rescue” her but really just looking for an opportunity to perv. 

Someone write the au fic.

summary: i’m honestly so confused right now. where did people get the idea that sansa just decided for herself, with zero input from the...
body:
i’m honestly so confused right now. where did people get the idea that sansa just decided for herself, with zero input from the north, to be queen? why do you think they’d accept that? they literally just escaped a tyrant. do ya’ll really think they would’ve chosen anybody else? who? i mean, they’ve tried multiple times to make her queen, have consistently recognised how she’s the person looking after their interests and safety, and it’s been made quite clear to the audience they’d never bend for anybody but a stark. would they have preferred robb or jon? honestly, most likely. they’d definitely prefer at least robb but hey, that’s not an option. what we do know for a fact is that they preferred sansa to jon at one point and we know they were 100% willing to choose her over him until she denied them.

let’s be very, very clear here: sansa hasn’t betrayed anybody. sansa has put her family and the north before herself for almost 3 seasons straight now and has on multiple occasions tried to increase the security of the power of her family and people (often at the expense of herself). ya’ll have reached the point where you’re actively lying to yourself just so you can be salty. frankly it’s embarrassing.

summary: I just read an alleged GoT analysis where the writer claimed that Sansa hasn’t grown and hasn’t learned anything except “that...
body:
I just read an alleged GoT analysis where the writer claimed that Sansa hasn’t grown and hasn’t learned anything except “that she’s queen in her own right, rather than being wife to a king.“ and I’m just ???????? Like how do you even write that? How can someone think that Sansa hasn’t grown except that she’s learned one of the most important lessons of the entire show that has been hammered home through multiple female characters including but not limited to Sansa, Cersei, Daenerys, Yara, Margaery, and Olenna? Hell, multiple male characters have suffered because their grasp on power depended on their relationship to the truly powerful, including Little Finger, Tyrion, Theon, Viserys, Ned, and even Jon. The show has gone out of it’s way to explicitly state why queen in her own right vs queen because king’s wife matters. The obtuseness, istg. ‘she only learned a major theme the entire story hammered home again and again, why didn’t she grow????’

‘The character did not learn the lessons I wanted them to learn’ =/= ‘The character did not learn anything’

‘The character did not grow the way I wanted them too’ =/= ‘The character did not grow’

like, at least have the balls to admit that you’re just bitter because she was successful and your fave wasn’t.

summary: I’m so annoyed by everyone saying shit like “blah blah blah sansa only asked for the north to be independent because she knew...
body:
I’m so annoyed by everyone saying shit like “blah blah blah sansa only asked for the north to be independent because she knew the king was now her brother and he would give it to her”

Like, no. She asked BECAUSE he was her brother. If it was literally anyone other than one of the Starks, she wouldn’t bother with formalities and niceties. She’d declare independence without permission, and do whatever she needed to do to protect that independence. She wasn’t fucking around, regardless of if the new king was her brother or not.

The north has been operating as an independent kingdom since Robb was named king, and y’all are suddenly upset that Sansa is following through with what her and her family wanted this whole time? Bye
